rComments: Worst professor ever. Posts solutions 2 days before the midterm. Final was really hard and doesn't know how to teach properly. DON'T ever take a class taught by him, he's the worst!

He is an amazing prof. Although his assignments are quite difficult, he can give you hints if you go to his office hours, and those hints are really helpful. His tests are the easier form of the assignments. If you can do you assignments, you can totally ace the course.

His writing is awful and his assignments are extremely hard for second year's students. Actually, his test is 90% similar with the assignments he posted out. But unfortunately, his assignments are usually too hard to understand and the materials covered in this lecture are usually beyond this courses ( lots of things should be learnt in MAT344/301

He is a really nice person, and is very approachable outside of class. Assignments are extremely hard, but once you figured it out, you will do well in the tests. His tests are similar to his assignments(much easier though) and the practice questions he posted before each test. If you understand all the assignment questions, you will do very well.
